fields.customfield_10409: As a marketer, I would like all old ACC data to be purged upon the migration to ACS because it is no longer needed.
fields.description:
As markets migrate to ACS, wed like to purge all of the production data in TEST since it wont be needed anymore.

Additionally, the workflow created to purge production data should be done table by table. The market should be able to choose the sequence of deletes and the schedule (when a table needs to be deleted).

This story deals with the creation of the workflow that will later handle the purging of data, it will not lead to the workflow being executed until the market has given us the OK on when to purge data.

 

{color:#ff0000}***NOTE** For US this MUST be completed by year-end to be compliant with CA Data Protection Act which goes into effect 1/1/2020*{color}

*Requirement* - 'Reading Redemption codes from s3' WF shall wait for 5 minutes after it receives the external signal to execute.

fields.customfield_10409: VALIDATE - If a campaign is created in OCE and the payload is sent to TEST, the expectation is TEST should be able to read UTC date format provided by OCE as a global solution and all workflows should be able to execute automatically.
fields.description:
*Background and Context* - As part of a global solution for R6 when OCE sends the timezone payload to TEST it is being sent in UTC which is causing issues with the workflow within TEST to execute automatically as TEST only reads local time. As a work around OCE has made a code change temporary to send the payload to TEST in the local time zone so the push notifications will run automatically.

 

*Technical Analysis -*

Below is the technical analysis on the changes needed for the above requirement,

*Assumptions:*
 *  OCE will always convert the time send in UTC only
 *  For Germany OCE will convert Germany/BErlin time to UTC timezone and send it to TEST, TEST has to take that UTC time format and spawn the workflow
 * For Australia OCE will convert Australia/Sydney time to UTC timezone and send it to TEST, TEST has to take that UTC time format and spawn the workflow for different timezones

VALIDATE - If an R4 customer is migrated to R6, that customer no longer is targeted in the campaigns created in R4.

GIVEN: Market Plans to schedule National Push Campaign
WHEN: National Push Campaign is scheduled.
THEN: Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from the campaign delivery.

GIVEN: Market Plans to schedule Priority Push Campaign
WHEN: Priority Push Campaign is scheduled.
THEN: Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from the campaign delivery.

GIVEN: Market Plans to schedule New Offer Push Campaign
WHEN: New Offer Push Campaign is scheduled.
THEN: Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from the campaign delivery.

GIVEN: Market Plans to schedule Segmented Offer Campaign
WHEN: Segmented Offer Campaign is scheduled.
THEN: Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from sending offer associations to eCP .

GIVEN: Market Plans to schedule Segmented Offer Campaign
WHEN: Segmented Offer Campaign is scheduled and sent for approval.
THEN: The count on Approval email and campaign summary page on web-form should exclude customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' .

items.fromString:
*Background and Context* -

During the R4 and R6 co-existence phase, when a user migrates from R4 app to R6 app, DCS 1.0 (R4 stack) makes an profile update call to TEST 4.x (R4 stack) notifying that the user has migrated to R6. This is done by adding subscription id - 99 to the subscriptions block within the profile update call. Sample payload is attached. 

If a customer migrates to R6 app, below would be added to subscriptions block in the profile update call,

{color:#14892c}{{color}
 {color:#14892c} "sourceId": "MOT",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "subscriptionId": "99",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "subscriptionDesc": "MigratedToR6",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "optInStatus": "Y",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "optInDate": "2019-06-20T08:13:49",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "lastModifiedBy": "Lambda-User",{color}
 {color:#14892c} "lastModifiedAt": "2019-06-20T08:31:53"{color}
 {color:#14892c} }{color}

*Requirement -* 

TEST should be able to consume subscription id 99 and update the recipient schema accordingly for respective users.

TEST should introduce a new data attribute to the schema.
 * Name of the new attribute that will be mapped to subscription id 99 - 'MigratedToR6'
 * Attribute values should be in Binary with Values Yes or No.

Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from National Push Campaign.
 Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from Priority Push Campaign.
 Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from New Offer Push Campaign.
 Customers having 'MigratedToR6' = 'Yes' should be excluded from sending offer associations to eCP for segmented campaigns.

The targeted count on Approval Email should exclude customers who migrated to R6.

The targeted count on Segment Detail Report should also exclude customers who migrated to R6.

*Technical Analysis -*

Below is the technical analysis on the changes needed for the above requirement,
 * Schema changes
 * Changes to Batch Profile Workflow
 * Changes to TEST Proxy APIs
 * Changes to the campaign workflows to restrict outgoing based on the flag

*Assumptions:*
 * The flag would flow through DCS whenever a customer migrates to R6 app.
 * The restriction would apply on mobile notifications and offer association.
 * There would not be any changes to reports/feeds generated within TEST.
 * If subscription id 99 is missing in the profile update call, it means that the user has not migrated to R6 yet.
 * By default, 'MigratedToR6' would be set to 'No' unless an update call happens with sub id 99 set to 'Y'.
 * The change does not apply to Milestone Campaigns.

items.toString:
*Background and Context* - As part of a global solution for R6 when OCE sends the timezone payload to TEST it is being sent in UTC which is causing issues with the workflow within TEST to execute automatically as TEST only reads local time. As a work around OCE has made a code change temporary to send the payload to TEST in the local time zone so the push notifications will run automatically.

 

*Technical Analysis -*

Below is the technical analysis on the changes needed for the above requirement,

*Assumptions:*
 *  OCE will always convert the time send in UTC only
 *  For Germany OCE will convert Germany/BErlin time to UTC timezone and send it to TEST, TEST has to take that UTC time format and spawn the workflow
 * For Australia OCE will convert Australia/Sydney time to UTC timezone and send it to TEST, TEST has to take that UTC time format and spawn the workflow for different timezones

fields.description:
Issue: Location calls are not processed if it comes with a new device token that does not exist in app subscription table. Because the operation to process this call is 'Update' only.

Solution: When a location call reaches TEST proxy, regardless the device token is new or existing, it should be upserted (Updated or Inserted) in to TEST db considering eCP ID as the unique key.

TEST Proxy should pass the service Id in the location call in the batch file as service Id should be inserted into db for the new registration.

Exception case - If the record comes in with eCP id 0 and new registration token, it will be rejected.

fields.description:
Register in the DE MTE App,

 
 # Login to the account
 # Do the Profile Update 

Actual Result: User should get the Profile Update emails When the RTC_AccountUpdateVerification is YNN

 

*Acceptance Criteria*:

GIVEN Customer wants to update his/her profile.
 WHEN Customer Updates First Name or Last Name or Zip Code on TESTGM.
 THEN Customer should receive 'Account Update Verification' Email.

*Assumption*:

Email field will always exist in 'Updated Fields' block in Update Profile Event ([https://us-confluence.TEST.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=AT&title=Account+Transformation+-+DCS+2.0+Event+Directory#AccountTransformation-DCS2.0EventDirectory-EventstoCIM]) from DCS.
